  "text": "Taking the example of the two-loop double box, we find two soft regions by taking the limit of either loop. We find a soft singularity whenever we have two adjacent massless legs in one of the loop integrations. In each case, we factorise into an IR divergent triangle and a dimension-shifted box: + O( ), (6.7) [CITATION_1] and summing the two regions, we quickly arrive at the result:",
